---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import FaqItem from "../components/FaqItem.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ — HermeΣ"
  description="Frequently asked questions about HermeΣ — setup, requirements, data privacy, accuracy, billing, and support for Greek chapter automation."
>
  <section class="bg-grid px-6 pt-20 pb-16 text-center md:px-12">
    <p class="fade-up text-gold mb-5 text-xs font-medium tracking-[5px] uppercase">FAQ</p>
    <h1 class="fade-up fade-up-d1 font-display text-[clamp(48px,8vw,84px)] leading-none tracking-[4px] text-white">
      Questions, <span class="text-gold">answered.</span>
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 pb-24 md:px-12" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-3xl flex-col gap-4">
      <FaqItem question="What does my chapter need to use HermeΣ?" class="reveal">
        Two things you almost certainly already have: a Slack workspace and a Google Calendar.
        HermeΣ plugs into both during onboarding — there's no new app for your members to download
        or learn.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="How long does setup take?" class="reveal">
        Setup happens during a single onboarding call. We connect your minutes channel and your
        chapter calendar, run a test PDF together, and you're live — typically the same week you
        sign up.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do members have to change how they work?" class="reveal">
        No. The only "step" is one your chapter already does: posting the meeting-minutes PDF to
        Slack. Everything after that — the summary, the action items, the calendar updates — is
        automatic.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What format do our minutes need to be in?" class="reveal">
        PDF is the supported format today. HermeΣ works with the minutes your secretary already
        produces — there's no required template, though consistent formatting makes extraction even
        sharper.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What happens to our data? Who can see our minutes?" class="reveal">
        HermeΣ only reads the specific channel you designate — nothing else in your workspace. Your
        minutes are processed solely to generate your chapter's summaries and calendar events.
        They're never sold and never used for anything beyond serving your chapter. See our
        <a href="/privacy" class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">Privacy Policy</a> for
        the full picture.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What if the AI gets something wrong?" class="reveal">
        Summaries post to Slack where the whole chapter can see them, so anything off gets caught
        immediately — and calendar events are normal Google Calendar events anyone with access can
        edit. In practice, clear minutes produce highly accurate output, and accuracy improves as
        your format stays consistent.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="How does billing work?" class="reveal">
        One flat price per chapter, billed monthly — no per-member fees and no long-term contract.
        Cancel anytime. Semester billing is also available, which many chapters find easier to run
        through their budget. See <a href="/pricing" class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">pricing</a>.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Can our council or national organization deploy HermeΣ across chapters?" class="reveal">
        Yes — that's the Council &amp; Nationals plan: multi-chapter deployment with centralized
        administration and dedicated support. <a href="/demo" class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">Contact us</a>
        and we'll scope it together.
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What support do we get?" class="reveal">
        Every plan includes email support. Chapter Plus adds priority response and a white-glove
        onboarding call. Either way, you can always reach us at
        <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`} class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
      </FaqItem>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-navy-mid px-6 py-24 text-center md:px-12">
    <h2 class="reveal font-display mb-6 text-[clamp(40px,6vw,64px)] leading-none tracking-[3px] text-white">
      Still curious? <span class="text-gold">Ask us live.</span>
    </h2>
    <div class="reveal reveal-d1">
      <Button href="/demo">Book a Demo</Button>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
